# Git & SSH Best Practices

## SSH Keys - Never Commit

- **Never** commit private keys (`id_ed25519`, `new`, or any file without `.pub`)
- **Never** commit `.pub` files in the project root—keep keys in `~/.ssh/`
- If keys were committed: `git rm --cached <file>`, add to `.gitignore`, commit removal
- Generate keys in default location: `ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "your@email.com"` then press Enter for defaults

## Passphrase

- Use empty passphrase for convenience, or set one for extra security
- If you forget the passphrase: generate a new key pair and add the new public key to GitHub

## GitHub Authentication

- Use SSH (not HTTPS) for push/pull: `git remote set-url origin git@github.com:user/repo.git`
- Add key to agent: `ssh-add ~/.ssh/id_ed25519` (or path to your key)
- Verify: `ssh -T git@github.com`

## .gitignore

Ensure these are ignored: `new`, `new.pub`, `*.pem`, `.env`, `node_modules`, `.next`
